OL,6,FShe heard him stealing from her
OL,7,Fjewellery box and confronted him as
OL,8,Fshe stood in the hallway.
OL,10,FAs she challenged the burglar, she
OL,11,Fcalled her 78-year-old daughter, who
OL,12,Farrived minutes later to confront the
OL,13,Fburglar in the bedroom.
OL,15,FAllanson pretended to be a police
OL,16,Fofficer and held up some kind of
OL,17,Fidentification badge, claiming he was
OL,18,Flooking for drugs.
